snippet.textDisplay: This maybe an ugly solution to a dust filter but most PC cases are the size of your standard house heater furnace filter.  Why can't one of those be one side of the case.  The case front back and top fans can suck the air out.  With that much filter surface area there should be almost no flow restriction.  And those filters are cheap and they come in all kinds of sizes and filtration level.  Get one that's HEPA and you'll have no dust.
